        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 1:30PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 130 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Spring Hill, or near Midway, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Midway, Pickett, Spring Hill, Comer, Barbour County Public Lake Dam,
Lugo, Three Notch, Batesville, and Mount Andrew.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
